
## ğŸ“„ **How to Deploy Guide**

```markdown
# ğŸš€ DEPLOYMENT GUIDE - Veterinary Clinic Website

## Step 1: Prepare Your Files

1. **Update WhatsApp Number** (MOST IMPORTANT!)
   - Open `js/main.js`
   - Find: `const WHATSAPP_NUMBER = '2348012345678';`
   - Replace with YOUR number (international format, no + or spaces)
   - Example: For +234 801 234 5678, use: `2348012345678`

2. **Replace Placeholder Text**
   - Search and replace `[Your Clinic Name]` with your actual clinic name
   - Search and replace `[Your Name]` with your name
   - Search and replace `[Your City, State]` with your location
   - Search and replace `your-email@example.com` with your email

3. **Add Your Images**
   - Create folder: `/assets/images/`
   - Replace all Unsplash URLs with your own images
   - Recommended images:
     - `hero.jpg` - Main banner image (1200x800px)
     - Product images (600x400px each)
     - `vet-photo.jpg` - Your photo (optional, square 400x400px)
     - `og-image.jpg` - Social media preview (1200x630px)

4. **Update Google Maps**
   - Go to Google Maps
   - Search for your address
   - Click "Share" â†’ "Embed a map"
   - Copy the iframe src URL
   - Paste in the map section of index.html

5. **Update Prices & Services**
   - Edit the Services & Prices section
   - Update product prices in the gallery
   - Modify opening hours

6. **Get Your Google Review Link**
   - Claim your Google Business Profile
   - Get your review link (format: https://g.page/r/YOUR_ID/review)
   - Replace in the Reviews section

## Step 2: Deploy to a Host

### Option A: Netlify (Easiest - Free)
1. Go to https://www.netlify.com
2. Sign up (free account)
3. Drag and drop your folder
4. Your site is live instantly!
5. Get a free subdomain or connect custom domain

### Option B: Vercel (Free)
1. Go to https://vercel.com
2. Sign up with GitHub
3. Import your project
4. Deploy automatically

### Option C: GitHub Pages (Free)
1. Create GitHub account
2. Create new repository
3. Upload files
4. Enable GitHub Pages in settings
5. Access at: `https://yourusername.github.io/repo-name`

### Option D: Surge.sh (Super Simple)
1. Install Node.js
2. Run: `npm install -g surge`
3. Run: `surge` in your project folder
4. Follow prompts - done!

### Option E: Traditional Hosting (cPanel, etc.)
1. Login to your hosting control panel
2. Go to File Manager
3. Upload all files to `public_html` folder
4. Access via your domain

## Step 3: Test Everything

After deployment, test:
- âœ… All WhatsApp links work (should open WhatsApp with pre-filled message)
- âœ… Phone numbers are clickable
- âœ… Email links work
- âœ… Google Maps loads correctly
- âœ… All images display
- âœ… Mobile responsive (test on phone)
- âœ… Navigation smooth scroll works

## Step 4: SEO & Marketing

1. **Update Meta Tags**
   - Confirm title, description, and keywords in index.html
   - Update Open Graph image URL

2. **Update JSON-LD Schema**
   - Scroll to bottom of index.html
   - Update business details (name, phone, address, coordinates)

3. **Google Business Profile**
   - Claim/create your profile at business.google.com
   - Add photos, hours, services
   - Match information with your website

4. **Share Your Website**
   - Add to your WhatsApp status
   - Share on social media
   - Add to business cards
   - Include in email signature

